# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — ECM_manuscript
# =============================================================================
# This repo provides the code to reproduce the analysis pipeline. It does not
# store data (raw or derived) or manuscript/Supplemental Information files —
# see README.md > Project structure for the rationale.

# ---- History / session files -------------------------------------------------
.Rhistory
.Rapp.history
.RData
.RDataTmp

# ---- User- and machine-specific files ----------------------------------------
.Rproj.user/
.Ruserdata

# ---- macOS metadata -----------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store

# ---- Secrets --------------------------------------------------------------
# API keys (ENTREZ_KEY, GBIF_USER, etc. — see README.md > API keys) must never
# be committed. Project-level .Renviron/.httr-oauth are ignored as a backstop,
# even though the README instructs storing keys in ~/.Renviron (outside the repo).
.Renviron
.httr-oauth

# ---- renv ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# renv.lock, renv/activate.R, and renv/settings.json ARE tracked (renv's own
# recommended git setup — they let a clone reproduce the exact package library
# via renv::restore()). Only the private library/cache dirs are ignored.
renv/library/
renv/local/
renv/cellar/
renv/lock/
renv/python/
renv/staging/

# ---- Raw data -------------------------------------------------------------
# Read-only external inputs (~17 GB; GlobalFungi, WorldClim, etc. — see
# data_raw/DATA-DICTIONARY.md). Not stored on GitHub; archived separately at
# an appropriate data repository. The dictionary itself IS tracked so the
# pipeline's inputs are documented even without the data present.
data_raw/*
!data_raw/DATA-DICTIONARY.md

# ---- Derived data -----------------------------------------------------------
# Every file here is regenerated from data_raw/ by scripts/run_all.R (checkpoint
# files alone run to ~1 GB). Not stored on GitHub. The dictionary itself IS
# tracked so the pipeline's outputs are documented without regenerating them.
data_derived/*
!data_derived/DATA-DICTIONARY.md

# ---- Figures ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Regenerated by scripts/run_all.R (Figure-xx_*.png). Not stored on GitHub.
figures/*

# ---- Manuscript & Supplemental Information -------------------------------
# Prepared and archived separately for journal submission (see README.md >
# Project structure) — this repo's scope is the analysis pipeline, not the
# manuscript text. Covers the qmd sources, every rendered format, and the
# shared bibliography/citation style.
*manuscript.*
*supplemental_information_S1*
*supplemental_information_S2*
references.bib
harvard-cite-them-right.csl

# ---- Quarto / R Markdown render artifacts --------------------------------
# In case the manuscript/SI docs are rendered locally in this folder.
*_files/
*_cache/
/cache/
*.utf8.md
*.knit.md

# ---- FACETS submission working folder ----------------------------------------
# Journal-submission scratch space (FACETS-compliant Quarto sources, an editable
# tables document, and rendered figure/table sets). Kept out of the repo: it is
# a submission-prep workspace derived from the tracked pipeline, not part of it.
FACETS/

# ---- Claude Code -------------------------------------------------------------
.claude/
